<TITLE> BDR man dies at Peelkhana </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 2 (bdnews24.com)A member of the Bangladesh Rifles died of heart failure at the force's Peelkhana headquarters on Sunday, a BDR official said. The deceased was identified as 47-year-old Habildar Md Shahidullah. He was discovered unconscious on the floor of a bathroom in the early hours, said Muhammad Mohsin Reza, the BDR's public relations officer. Shahidullah was rushed to the BDR hospital where doctors pronounced him dead, said the official. Reza said the death brought the number of BDR members who had died since February's mutiny to 35. The 35 deaths have been ascribed to suicides, cardiac arrests and other causes by authorities. bd
